.TH "pwm_request_from_chip" 9 "pwm_request_from_chip" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pwm_request_from_chip \- request a PWM device relative to a PWM chip
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct pwm_device *" pwm_request_from_chip
.BI "(struct pwm_chip *chip "  ","
.BI "unsigned int index "  ","
.BI "const char *label "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chip" 12
PWM chip
.IP "index" 12
per-chip index of the PWM to request
.IP "label" 12
a literal description string of this PWM
.SH "RETURN"
A pointer to the PWM device at the given index of the given PWM
chip. A negative error code is returned if the index is not valid for the
specified PWM chip or if the PWM device cannot be requested.
